%N A072521 a(1) = 6 and then the smallest triangular numbers, larger than the previous term, such that sum of two neighbors is also a triangular number.
%C A072521 The sequence is unbounded as a(n+1) is at most the a(n)-th triangular number.
%C A072521 If a(n) + u*(u+1)/2 = t*(t+1)/2 then 2*a(n) = (t-u)*(t+u+1) so t-u and t+u+1 are divisors of 2*a(n) and t-u and t+u+1 have different parity. - _David A. Corneth_, Jan 06 2026
%H A072521 Robert Israel, <a href="/A072521/b072521.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..359</a>
%e A072521 45 is a term because 21 + 45 = 66, 45 + 91 = 136, and 66 and 136 are triangular numbers.
%p A072521 R:= 6: r:= 6: s:= 3:
%p A072521 for i from 1 to 30 do
%p A072521   s:= min(select(`>`,map(subs,{isolve(1 + 8*r + 4*y*(y+1) = z^2)},y),s));
%p A072521   r:= s*(s+1)/2;
%p A072521   R:= R,r
%p A072521 od:
%p A072521 R; # _Robert Israel_, Jan 05 2026
%o A072521 (PARI) p=6; k=3; print1(p", "); for(n=1, 30, k=k+1; u=p+k*(k+1)/2; t=sqrtint(2*u); while(u!=t*(t+1)/2, k=k+1; u=p+k*(k+1)/2; t=sqrtint(2*u)); p=k*(k+1)/2; print1(p", "))
%o A072521 (PARI) first(n) = {my(res=List([6])); for(i=2, n-1, listput(res, nxt(res[#res])));res}
%o A072521 nxt(n) = {my(d = divisors(2*n), u); forstep(i = (#d + 1)\2, 1, -1, if(bitand(d[i]+d[#d + 1 - i], 1), u = (d[#d + 1 - i] - 1 - d[i])/2; c = u*(u+1)/2; if(c > n, return(c))))} \\ _David A. Corneth_, Jan 06 2026
